projects.description: Member of the organising committee of the first SUMMA symposium: ' Let Food be thy medicine, and medicine be thy food''. On June 17th 2014, the first SUMMA symposium was held at the UMC Utrecht. This year the theme was: 'let food be thy medicine and medicine be thy food'. During the symposium several lectures and master classes were given about the relationship between nutrition and medicine by experts in this field. Speakers: Prof. Dr. Eggersdorfer (senior vice president DSM) Prof. Dr. Garssen (Director platform Immunology, Nutricia research) Prof. Dr. Kersten (Wageningen University) Dr. L.M. Broersen: (Danone Research).

volunteer_experiences.description: Teddy bear Doctors is a roleplay in which children lying in the hospital crawl in the role of doctor to heal their sick teddy bears. The purpose of teddy bear doctors is to destract the sick children in the WKZ of their diseases and to reduce their anxiety for doctors.

Kindergarten classes visit the WKZ with their 'sick' stuffed animals to make them better. The purpose of Teddy Bear Hospital is to get children acquainted with health care in a playfull manner, to diminish the fear of doctors and being sick.
PhUn Day (Physiology Understand) at Children's Museum Jackson Mississippi
